BBC.Later.with.Jool.Holland.S44E01.1080i.h264-NX

BBC 2 HD Friday 18th April 2014

Jools Holland returns for a run of seven episodes. Joining Jools are Elbow who will be making a welcome return to the show with numbers from their recent chart-topping album The Take Off And Landing of Everything. Neneh Cherry performs tracks from her long-awaited solo album Blank Project, which features collaborations with Four Tet and Robyn, plus her classic 1988 tune Buffalo Stance. From Leeds, and making their UK TV debut, will be post-punk five piece Eagulls, whose songs mix their anger and discomfort at all around them through their stark lyrics. Leicestershire's own Engelbert Humperdinck joins the line-up with a chat and a classic number at the piano. Cambridge-based baroque-house-pop foursome Clean Bandit performing one of the biggest singles of the year already in Rather Be with vocalist Jess Glynne. Danish singer-songwriter and pianist Agnes Obel, whose debut album Aventine saw her sweep up various accolades across Europe.
